    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const title = $('Code3').first().json.title;\nconst description = $('Code3').first().json.description;\n\nconst prompt = `You are a JSON generator. You must return only valid JSON, nothing else.\n\nGiven this content:\nTitle: ${title}\nDescription: ${description}\nSource: YouTube\n\nReturn a JSON object with exactly these fields:\n- summary: a comprehensive summary of 2-4 sentences that captures the main topic, key points, and value of the video. Be specific — mention concepts, tools, or techniques discussed if present in the description. Do not use vague filler sentences.\n- tags: array of 2-4 topic tags in lowercase\n- content_type: one of these exact strings: \"tutorial\", \"news\", \"tool\", \"concept\", \"case-study\", \"opinion\"\n\nRules:\n- All string values must be in double quotes\n- No trailing commas\n- No text outside the JSON object\n- If the description is short or vague, infer context from the title\n\nExample output:\n{\n  \"summary\": \"Comprehensive summary of the video content based on title and description.\",\n  \"tags\": [\"tag1\", \"tag2\"],\n  \"content_type\": \"tutorial\"\n}`;\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    model: \"llama-3.3-70b-versatile\",\n    messages: [\n      {\n        role: \"user\",\n        content: prompt\n      }\n    ],\n    temperature: 0.3\n  }\n}];"
      },
